data.name: btnPresetLoadTags.ToolTip
data.value: Load presets based on tags filter Examples: "calm, chill, dark" -> match any of these tags "calm & dark" -> must match both of there tags "calm & !colorful" -> must match first tag and may not contain second

data.name: lblVisIntensity.ToolTip
data.value: A parameter introduced by Milkwave which presets can read to adjust the intensity of a preset effect For Milkwaves "Shader" presets, this will adjust how much the preset reacts to audio input Click: Set 1 Hold Alt while changing value: Set increment to 0.05

data.name: lblVisShift.ToolTip
data.value: A parameter introduced by Milkwave which presets can use to "shift" a preset effect For Milkwaves "Shader" presets, this will adjust the initial value of the effect that is linked to the audio signal Click: Set 0 Hold Alt while chaning value: Set increment to 0.05

data.name: lblVisVersion.ToolTip
data.value: A parameter introduced by Milkwave which presets can use to present a different version For Milkwaves "Shader" presets this means: Version = 1: Effect depends on value of "bass_smooth" (slow reaction) Version = 2: Effect depends on value of "bass_att" (fast and intense reaction) Version > 2: No audio reaction (will still respond to "Intensity" and "Shift" changes) Click: Set 1

data.name: lblMidi1Inc.ToolTip
data.value: For knobs and faders, this is the amount the target control will be changed with every MIDI step (0-127) The default value of a control (eg. 1.0 for "Intensity") is assigned to the "middle setting" of the fader/knob (MIDI step 64) See the Milkwave manual for details (press "?" button)

data.name: lblQuality.ToolTip
data.value: Adjust the render quality This setting has no effect if Spout is both "Active" and "Fixed"! A lower value saves GPU time and gives a pixellated look Click: Set 1 Hold Alt while changing value: Set increment to 0.05
